This section, and hopefully the unitary one too, should go in `Algebra.Algebra.Spectrum`, preferably even in another PR.
I was *wondering* if you were going to suggest this. Cool!
This section as should go in the same file as the theorems used to prove these, preferably in another PR.
This section should go in another file, although I'm not sure which is best off the top of my head. This should also constitute another PR.
Some of these spectrum/eigenvalue results can probably go in the `Matrix.IsHermitian` file.
Should I do this as part of the main PR? If so, I'd like to know why you think so, i.e. why is this different than the above sections you suggested that I PR separately?
I was only able to move one of these, as the others require `spectrum` so would need an import. What do you suggest?
This shouldn't be called `phi` it either needs to be inlined, or given a more informative name. Also, have you considered defining it on bare functions instead of continuous ones?
Hmm. Let me think about what this might clean up...

I doubt it will clean up anything, but the advantage is that in the future we can write a lemma of the form `cfc f a = œÜ f` for *any* `f`, so long as `a` is selfadjoint. This is nice because the first argument to `cfc` is a bare function.

What do you mean by 'inclined' in this context? (I am inclined to give this a more informative name...)
(DOH! You wrote `inlined` not `inclined`....got it!)
I've changed the name to `cfc`. Now I have to look into changing this to bare functions...
It seems that if I replace the type of continuous functions to the type of bare functions, the instance declaration has several places where it expects a map on continuous functions.
Surely not all of these imports are necessary?
You are right! I winnowed this down to four.

```suggestion
`RCLike` field `ùïú`.
```

```suggestion
/-- The `‚Ñù`-spectrum of a Hermitian matrix over `RCLike` field is the range of the eigenvalue
function -/
```

```suggestion
/-- The star algebra homomorphism underlying the instance of the continuous functional
calculus of a Hermitian matrix. This is an auxiliary definition and is not intended
for use outside of this file. -/
```

```suggestion
- `Matrix.IsHermitian.instContinuousFunctionalCalculus` : Instance of the continuous functional
  calculus for a Hermitian matrix `A` over `ùïú`.
```

```suggestion
theorem eigenvalues_eq_spectrum_real {a : Matrix n n ùïú} (ha : IsHermitian a) :
    spectrum ‚Ñù a = Set.range (ha.eigenvalues) := by
```
